346
00:29:37,944 --> 00:29:42,345
- We'll clear a path to the sled.
Everybody ready?

347
00:29:43,945 --> 00:29:45,276
- One, two...

348
00:29:45,476 --> 00:29:49,211
Wait. No, no.
Stop.

349
00:29:49,311 --> 00:29:53,044
- I think they are the Gauol.

350
00:29:58,278 --> 00:30:01,012
Ahh.

351
00:30:05,744 --> 00:30:06,878
Over here!

352
00:30:06,978 --> 00:30:09,145
Quick little devil.

353
00:30:09,245 --> 00:30:11,845
- Okay, all I have to do is tap
into the central computer,

354
00:30:11,945 --> 00:30:13,945
and we can figure
the departure protocols.

355
00:30:14,045 --> 00:30:17,879
- Yes. Making progress.
Yes, I'm making progress.

356
00:30:17,979 --> 00:30:20,480
Huh? Wait, wait.

357
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:23,044
- Hmm.

358
00:30:23,144 --> 00:30:26,145
Ooh. Hmm.

359
00:30:48,445 --> 00:30:54,013
The moon, the moon, the moon. Right,
yeah. That's how we knew to come here.

360
00:30:54,813 --> 00:30:57,780
My father made a map
with that moon on it.

361
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:01,245
Now, why? Is the ship
hidden there?

362
00:31:04,379 --> 00:31:07,847
Ohh.

363
00:31:09,313 --> 00:31:12,148
- Oh.

364
00:31:21,146 --> 00:31:23,980
Hmm. Ahh.

365
00:31:28,148 --> 00:31:31,348
It must be somewhere
in the Andali Nebula.

366
00:31:33,848 --> 00:31:35,715
We did it, kid.

367
00:31:35,815 --> 00:31:38,980
The Titan is as good
as ours.

368
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:42,780
He must have been here, standing here.
Right here.

369
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:46,447
- Who?
- My father.

370
00:31:50,615 --> 00:31:52,615
Go!

371
00:31:56,380 --> 00:31:59,514
Let's move it!

372
00:32:00,214 --> 00:32:02,515
We've gotta
get to the beach!

373
00:32:35,314 --> 00:32:36,148
- Akima!

374
