- Why aren't they shooting at Cale?
- They want him alive.

375
00:32:56,983 --> 00:33:00,483
Come on, guys.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

376
00:33:16,583 --> 00:33:18,584
Nice catch.

377
00:33:28,385 --> 00:33:30,118
Pull up! Pull up!

378
00:33:59,652 --> 00:34:02,252
Preed, come in!
Preed, where are you?

379
00:34:02,352 --> 00:34:04,519
- Hold on!

380
00:34:06,419 --> 00:34:09,884
- Preed, come in!

381
00:34:10,584 --> 00:34:13,785
- Preed!

382
00:34:16,352 --> 00:34:21,119
Preed, Preed, Preed! Aren't you
supposed to be watching for the Drej?

383
00:34:21,219 --> 00:34:25,187
Yes, caveman, that's right.
Drej bad. We good.

384
00:34:25,286 --> 00:34:28,484
- Now, go look at
something shiny for a while.

385
00:34:28,584 --> 00:34:31,085
- How's this?

386
00:34:31,218 --> 00:34:34,419
- Well, you'd better look again!

387
00:34:37,286 --> 00:34:38,219
Drej!

388
00:34:38,319 --> 00:34:41,019
- Aah!

389
00:35:02,087 --> 00:35:04,488
Captain, we're on our way.
Where are you?

390
00:35:04,586 --> 00:35:07,152
We're in the
hydrogen trees being chased by the Drej.

391
00:35:07,452 --> 00:35:09,787
- See if you can spot them, quick!
- Look there!

392
00:35:13,421 --> 00:35:15,554
- Akima!
- Hang on!

393
00:35:24,919 --> 00:35:26,953
Nice move.

394
00:35:31,853 --> 00:35:33,520
Get down!

395
00:35:38,954 --> 00:35:41,422
Come on.
Show yourselves.

396
00:35:43,853 --> 00:35:45,821
- Get down!
- Cale!

397
00:35:48,454 --> 00:35:50,654
- I got 'em.

398
00:35:52,921 --> 00:35:54,888
Whoa!

399
00:35:55,289 --> 00:35:57,889
Preed, look!
There they are!

400
00:35:59,990 --> 00:36:01,787
Oh, no.

401
00:36:04,288 --> 00:36:08,889
- Hang on, Akima!

402
00:36:10,989 --> 00:36:13,489
Don't shoot!

403
00:36:13,622 --> 00:36:16,190
Don't shoot!
They've got Cale!

404
00:36:21,487 --> 00:36:24,787
Gune, calculate their trajectory.
Stith, take weapons.

405
00:36:24,888 --> 00:36:27,822
- Let's get on it, people.
- Oh, nice job covering our butts, Preed.

406
00:36:27,921 --> 00:36:31,189
- You're the weapons expert.
- What were you doing? Taking a nap?

407
00:36:31,289 --> 00:36:34,923
Enough! Okay,
the Drej took Cale.

408
00:36:35,023 --> 00:36:37,756
But they are not
gonna get away with it.

409
00:36:37,890 --> 00:36:41,022
Well, let's quit running
our collective mouths and go get him.

410
00:36:41,155 --> 00:36:46,489
Our only chance to locate them
is to track Akima. Stith, get on it.

411
00:36:51,490 --> 00:36:53,390
Hmm.

412
00:36:53,990 --> 00:36:56,924
They're gonna use you to figure out
where the Titan is.

413
00:36:58,223 --> 00:37:01,856
Probably just blow it up,
too, when they find it.

414
00:37:01,956 --> 00:37:06,790
- Yeah, well, who's to say it would've worked, anyway?
- Who's to say it won't?

415
00:37:07,790 --> 00:37:11,291
Maybe Korso will get
to the Titan first.

416
00:37:11,391 --> 00:37:14,191
Why do you care so much
about that thing?

417
00:37:15,492 --> 00:37:18,156
I was raised
around people.

418
00:37:18,255 --> 00:37:21,756
"Drifter Colony bums",
I believe, is the term.

419
00:37:24,023 --> 00:37:28,857
I barely remember Earth, but the older
ones used to tell us about it...

420
00:37:28,957 --> 00:37:31,991
so it would never
be completely lost.

421
00:37:32,491 --> 00:37:35,890
No matter how hard things got-
and they were hard...

422
00:37:35,990 --> 00:37:39,057
those memories
kept us going.

423
00:37:39,157 --> 00:37:42,591
Once, we had a home.

424
00:37:43,991 --> 00:37:47,591
The Titan is our chance
to find one again.

425
00:37:50,925 --> 00:37:53,892
I guess that's how
I ended up here.

426
00:37:53,992 --> 00:37:58,291
What are they afraid of? So what did
the human race ever do to the Drej?

427
00:37:58,391 --> 00:38:02,492
- It's not what we did. They're afraid of
what we might become. - Hmm.

428
00:38:02,592 --> 00:38:05,892
Yeah, well, looks like
we're becoming extinct.

429
00:38:53,926 --> 00:38:57,193
- Cale, you okay?

430
00:38:59,093 --> 00:39:00,394
- Akima!

431
00:39:04,861 --> 00:39:07,294
Cale!

432
00:40:03,763 --> 00:40:07,494
- Cale!
